is the gun actually
has a special property.

784
01:04:20,423 --> 01:04:21,981
The revolution
depends on this weapon...

785
01:04:24,193 --> 01:04:26,559
The gun freezes people.

786
01:04:26,629 --> 01:04:28,256
Interesting.

787
01:04:30,399 --> 01:04:32,765
So, what happens next?

788
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:40,198
Incoming call on cine-com.

789
01:04:42,979 --> 01:04:45,880
Do you have possession
of the package? Please respond.

790
01:04:45,948 --> 01:04:47,108
Affirmative.

791
01:05:07,837 --> 01:05:09,464
I'm sorry.

792
01:05:09,538 --> 01:05:11,563
Bring it down. You all right?

793
01:05:11,641 --> 01:05:14,132
Sorry, I didn't realize...
I'm fine. My foot...

794
01:05:14,210 --> 01:05:15,802
All right, we'll go again.

795
01:05:15,878 --> 01:05:17,470
It was our fault.
Bring her up, please.

796
01:06:29,518 --> 01:06:32,078
Someone stole the exposed film.

797
01:06:49,605 --> 01:06:51,539
Paul, go.

798
01:06:51,607 --> 01:06:53,802
Here.

799
01:07:55,971 --> 01:07:57,529
Are you scared?

800
01:08:10,286 --> 01:08:12,151
Oops.

801
01:08:28,170 --> 01:08:29,933
-You OK?
-Yeah.

802
01:08:30,005 --> 01:08:32,098
-You sure?
-I'm fine.

803
01:08:44,353 --> 01:08:45,684
Go.

804
01:09:23,959 --> 01:09:25,586
How could you betray me?

805
01:09:25,661 --> 01:09:28,289
Destroy my artwork,
you little shit!

806
01:09:28,364 --> 01:09:31,026
Do you think that you can
make a better ending...

807
01:09:31,100 --> 01:09:33,568
by putting in your car chase?

808
01:09:33,636 --> 01:09:36,605
What about the theme?
The story?

809
01:09:36,672 --> 01:09:38,071
Have you
thought about that, Paul?

810
01:09:38,140 --> 01:09:39,437
-I wasn't trying...
-Bullshit!

811
01:09:39,508 --> 01:09:42,500
Don't move! I'm warning you!

812
01:09:47,082 --> 01:09:48,674
I'm sorry.

813
01:09:48,751 --> 01:09:51,618
It's a big opportunity for me...

814
01:09:51,687 --> 01:09:54,019
You want
to knowthe real reason?

815
01:09:54,089 --> 01:09:57,183
They are afraid about the film.

816
01:09:57,259 --> 01:10:00,228
They're trying to keep
the youth rebellion suppressed.

817
01:10:00,296 --> 01:10:04,062
A film can change
the course of the future.

818
01:10:04,133 --> 01:10:09,503
It can invent the future
by making ideas concrete.

819
01:10:09,572 --> 01:10:13,030
That's why when I heard
you were changing the ending...

820
01:10:13,108 --> 01:10:14,700
I was forced to do this.

821
01:10:14,777 --> 01:10:16,039
I had an idea.

822
01:10:16,111 --> 01:10:18,978
I had a new idea for the ending,
that maybe she...

823
01:10:19,048 --> 01:10:22,916
the Corporation, its center,
betrays her.

824
01:10:30,292 --> 01:10:34,558
The revolutionary get
their weapon back in the end.

825
01:10:34,630 --> 01:10:37,258
Promise me that, Paul.

826
01:10:42,504 --> 01:10:44,995
I promise.

827
01:10:47,209 --> 01:10:48,540
Good.

828
01:10:51,380 --> 01:10:54,178
I've been working
on a personal film.

829
01:10:54,250 --> 01:10:56,548
Personal film?

830
01:10:56,619 --> 01:10:59,087
With no compromise, right?

831
01:10:59,154 --> 01:11:01,679
-Right.
-We'll...

832
01:11:01,757 --> 01:11:03,816
see about you.

833
01:11:05,594 --> 01:11:07,494
I'm old.

834
01:11:07,563 --> 01:11:11,021
I can go now and write
my personal work.

835
01:11:13,869 --> 01:11:18,431
Nowthat I have something
to write about.

836
01:11:24,413 --> 01:11:26,176
I have to ask...

837
01:11:29,118 --> 01:11:31,052
Did you make love to her?

838
01:11:35,891 --> 01:11:38,826
Did you cut the brakes
on Felix's car?

839
01:11:46,535 --> 01:11:49,003
Remember, Paul...

840
01:11:49,071 --> 01:11:52,666
always stand
next to the camera.

841
01:11:52,741 --> 01:11:55,369
Your actor
will feel you there...

842
01:11:55,444 --> 01:11:58,811
and will be playing
just for you.

843
01:12:08,791 --> 01:12:10,918
I can't believe it.

844
01:12:10,993 --> 01:12:12,858
Bravo! Did they catch him?

845
01:12:12,928 --> 01:12:14,259
Who was the son of a bitch
who stole the film?

846
01:12:14,330 --> 01:12:15,558
Just some old guy.

847
01:12:15,631 --> 01:12:18,725
It doesn't matter anyway.
We got it back.

848
01:12:18,801 --> 01:12:20,132
It's all going to work out.

849
01:12:20,202 --> 01:12:23,330
We'll get the final footage
tomorrow on the stage.

850
01:12:23,405 --> 01:12:26,772
-You did good, Paul.
-Where's Valentine? Is she OK?

851
01:12:26,842 --> 01:12:30,243
She was fine. In fact,
I think she enjoyed herself.

852
01:12:30,312 --> 01:12:32,644
She just left in a rush.

853
01:12:32,715 --> 01:12:35,047
She asked that you call her.

854
01:12:35,117 --> 01:12:37,847
She said it was important.

855
01:12:37,920 --> 01:12:40,821
Antonio, come on, eh?

856
01:12:47,429 --> 01:12:48,828
Hi, it's Paul.

857
01:12:48,897 --> 01:12:50,990
You got to come here quickly.

858
01:12:51,066 --> 01:12:52,533
Oh, my God!

859
01:12:57,573 --> 01:12:58,835
Taxi!

860
01:13:16,925 --> 01:13:18,893
Come look.

861
01:13:30,372 --> 01:13:32,237
They were just born.

862
01:13:40,282 --> 01:13:43,718
I like to document
all the things of my life.

863
01:15:04,299 --> 01:15:05,994
I found you.

864
01:15:09,671 --> 01:15:12,697
I was cold.

865
01:15:22,684 --> 01:15:24,208
Thank you very much.

866
01:15:30,058 --> 01:15:31,218
All right.

867
01:15:34,296 --> 01:15:35,456
And...

868
01:15:40,502 --> 01:15:41,730
And action.

869
01:15:59,087 --> 01:16:01,021
But how?

870
01:16:01,089 --> 01:16:03,523
You're me.

871
01:16:07,296 --> 01:16:09,230
Quickly, we're in danger.

872
01:16:10,265 --> 01:16:13,234
Nice try, Dragonfly.

873
01:16:13,302 --> 01:16:14,769
Go, go!

874
01:17:21,903 --> 01:17:24,133
My father built
the Dragonfly robot...

875
01:17:24,206 --> 01:17:26,436
for the most dangerous
missions.

876
01:17:26,508 --> 01:17:28,066
He modeled her on me...

877
01:17:28,143 --> 01:17:30,577
her looks and
her lifelike qualities.

878
01:17:30,646 --> 01:17:32,705
But the Corporation
programmed her...

879
01:17:32,781 --> 01:17:35,511
so that
she couldn't betray them.

880
01:17:35,584 --> 01:17:38,382
She wanted to help you,
but she couldn't.

881
01:17:38,453 --> 01:17:40,182
That's why I tried to help.

882
01:17:40,255 --> 01:17:42,780
I knewthe revolution
needed this weapon...

883
01:17:42,858 --> 01:17:45,190
so I took it to give to you.

884
01:17:45,260 --> 01:17:48,991
I did it to help you,
to help the cause.

885
01:17:49,064 --> 01:17:52,625
I believe in this revolution...

886
01:17:52,701 --> 01:17:55,465
and I believe in you.

887
01:17:57,406 --> 01:17:59,806
We were in love.

888
01:18:01,143 --> 01:18:04,601
We are identical
in all respects.

889
01:18:06,281 --> 01:18:07,714
In all respects?

890
01:18:07,783 --> 01:18:09,876
In all respects.

891
01:18:50,492 --> 01:18:53,256
All I really did was stitch
together things from my life.

892
01:18:53,328 --> 01:18:55,262
Things that made
an impression on me.

893
01:18:55,330 --> 01:18:57,764
Just put a little piece
of myself out there...

894
01:18:57,833 --> 01:18:59,460
try to organize it,
take a look at it...

895
01:18:59,534 --> 01:19:02,526
make some connections,
some sense of things.

896
01:19:02,604 --> 01:19:04,469
I think that's
all the time we have.

897
01:19:04,539 --> 01:19:05,972
Thanks a lot to Paul.

898
01:19:13,148 --> 01:19:15,207
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

899
01:19:15,283 --> 01:19:17,046
I enjoyed what you had to say.

900
01:19:17,119 --> 01:19:18,381
Thank you very much.

901
01:19:18,453 --> 01:19:21,581
By the way,
do you know Felix DeMarco?

902
01:19:23,058 --> 01:19:26,118
Do you think you could pass
this script on to him for me?

903
01:19:26,194 --> 01:19:29,163
-Sure.
-Thanks.

904
01:19:32,868 --> 01:19:36,235
My dog knocked over the tripod,
and the camera kept running...

905
01:19:36,304 --> 01:19:38,363
so I kept it all in the film.

906
01:19:46,248 --> 01:19:47,545
...things around you...

907
01:19:47,616 --> 01:19:49,083
as if that would bring
some understanding?

908
01:19:49,151 --> 01:19:51,745
I just want to capture
what's real and honest.

909
01:19:51,820 --> 01:19:53,685
And what if it's boring?

910
01:19:53,755 --> 01:19:55,154
Maybe Marlene was right...

911
01:19:55,223 --> 01:19:59,057
but each one of these images
brings up a feeling or a memory.

912
01:19:59,127 --> 01:20:03,063
I can smell Marlene when
I see this shot of the soap.

913
01:20:03,131 --> 01:20:05,964
I found her drivers license...

914
01:20:06,034 --> 01:20:08,366
and I tried to reach her
by calling her mother...

915
01:20:08,436 --> 01:20:10,233
and Marlene answered.

916
01:20:13,975 --> 01:20:17,001
When she heard my voice,
she hung up.

917
01:20:18,713 --> 01:20:21,307
I thought that my film
was going to be about...

918
01:20:21,383 --> 01:20:22,941
looking at
all the pieces of myself...

919
01:20:23,018 --> 01:20:25,077
but, Marlene...

920
01:20:25,153 --> 01:20:28,088
I got you in pieces, too.

921
01:20:33,728 --> 01:20:35,719
So this is the end...

922
01:20:35,797 --> 01:20:38,698
or is it the start?

923
01:20:38,767 --> 01:20:40,359
Of what?

